+{
+  "contract_id": "057",
+  "feature_id": "057",
+  "name": "Progress-comparison taxonomy amendment (NDEBT-022)",
+  "status": "approved",
+  "spec_ref": ".agent/product_spec_006.md",
+  "design_notes": {
+    "what_this_feature_is": "Phase-006 F-057: amend the LIVE ecosystem/07_progress_comparison.md (0.1.1 -> 0.2.0) to complete its finding-state taxonomy so a real corpus classifies without workarounds. Section 3 adds the fifth transition class `persisting` (present on both sides and still open, with evidence freshly re-confirmed at/after the later execution's anchors -- the exact opposite of `stale`; carried, never a source of score movement). Section 3.1 adds the pre-window-resolved recording rule (a finding resolved before the earlier input's own reference point is recorded with its closure evidence but is NOT a cross-execution transition and is excluded from the open-findings score; `resolved` is reserved for an in-window closure). Section 3.2 adds the first-comparison rule (an empty `reopened` bucket on a first-ever comparison is correct). Section 6.1 fixes the score-count semantics: the open-findings score counts `open` findings only, never resolved or pre-window-resolved recorded findings. Section 1/7 'four'->'five' transition classes; frontmatter description + change_log updated.",
+    "audit_044_mapping": "The amendment is motivated by and validated against audit-044 (the framework's first real comparison), whose committed delta bridged two gaps via unchanged_facts + prose notes. Under the amended taxonomy the five findings classify directly: F-audit044-ndebt-015 (open, re-confirmed this run) -> `persisting`; F-audit044-ndebt-002 (resolved 2026-07-10, before baseline #1's 2026-07-17 capture) -> pre-window-resolved (recorded, not a transition); F-audit044-ndebt-016 (stale evidence) -> `stale`; F-audit044-ndebt-017/018 -> `new`. The open-findings score is open-only 2->4 (015,016 -> 015,016,017,018; the resolved 002 excluded), with the +2 attributable to the two `new` findings -- exactly the movement the committed delta reported, now derivable without unchanged_facts.",
+    "immutability_note": "AH-3: the committed audit-2026-07-17-cba6422 artifacts (delta.json, findings.json, report.md) are NOT touched -- they honestly recorded the corpus under the old taxonomy with transparent notes, and stay immutable. The amendment binds FUTURE comparisons; E06 asserts zero change under .agent/audits/.",
+    "next_feature_decision": "The operator directed 'Rebase line approved' + 'Option 1' (2026-07-19), authorizing a Section-6/9 scope-budget re-baseline (original_estimate_lines 1720 -> 2300, ceiling 2236 -> 2990; recorded structurally in scope_budget.rebaselines in the separate commit 085e568) AND choosing to proceed with feature 057. So 057 is operator-selected, not abort-driven. The re-baseline gives the phase tail headroom without a mid-phase §6 halt.",
+    "process_honesty": "Single-session collapsed-role execution, disclosed-and-permitted by the AGF Orchestrator clause. The re-baseline is committed separately (085e568) as an Orchestrator coordination action before this feature's work, per NDEBT-018 (gate/coordination decisions committed to durable state promptly). E01/E07 anchor to the phase base 964fe48 (not HEAD~1), since the re-baseline commit sits between the base and this deliverable; E09 dogfoods the NDEBT-019 rc-capture rule.",
+    "review_round": "PR #35 CodeRabbit review (ASSERTIVE, CHANGES_REQUESTED, 4 Major, all valid, all addressed): (1) E01 anti-vacuity only checked persisting + 3.1 while its PASS message claimed 3.2/6.1 too -- now asserts the absence of all four sections at base. (2) E05 (the acceptance test) printed a hardcoded map and checked only two statuses -- now DERIVES every finding's amended class from the delta buckets + the amended rules and asserts all five, and derives the open-only scores (2->4) rather than hardcoding them. (3) E07's `grep -v '^.agent/'` left the dot unescaped (a wildcard) -- now `^\\.agent/`. (4) TAXONOMY: `new` and `reopened` overlapped for a previously-resolved finding that reappears -- ecosystem/07 Section 3 now makes `new` exclude previously-resolved findings and `reopened` the sole class for them, preserving the exactly-one-class rule (a real defect E05 could not catch, since audit-044 has no reopened case). Evidence re-captured for the review round; the original captures remain in git history at 0cd52fb."
+  },
+  "scope": {
+    "files_create": [],
+    "files_modify": [
+      {
+        "path": "ecosystem/07_progress_comparison.md",
+        "purpose": "0.2.0: add the fifth `persisting` transition class (Section 3), the pre-window-resolved recording rule (3.1), the first-comparison rule (3.2), and the open-vs-recorded score-count semantics (6.1); Section 1/7 four->five; frontmatter description + change_log."
+      },
+      {
+        "path": "docs/planning/DEBT.md",
+        "purpose": "0.26.0: NDEBT-022 Open -> Resolved with the resolution note."
+      },
+      {
+        "path": "CHANGELOG.md",
+        "purpose": "[Unreleased] Added: the progress-comparison taxonomy completion entry."
+      }
+    ]
+  },
