+    "No change to the committed audit-2026-07-17-cba6422 delta/findings/report artifacts -- they are immutable (AH-3); the amendment binds future comparisons only.",
+    "No new audit_delta.schema.json -- it remains a deferred, optional schema (product_spec_005 Section 2.3); this feature amends the protocol's prose semantics, not the JSON Schema.",
+    "No change to the meaning of the four existing transition classes (new/resolved/reopened/stale) beyond the `resolved` clarification (in-window closure) that the pre-window-resolved rule requires; no change to Sections 2, 4, 5, 8.",
+    "No change to any other ecosystem/ document or to the score weighting/thresholds a consumer defines on top of this protocol."
+  ],
+  "verification": [
+    {
+      "acceptance_test": "ANTI-VACUITY (phase base 964fe48 = the F-054 merge / PR #34): at the base ecosystem/07 was 0.1.1 with four transition classes and no `persisting`, Section 3.1/3.2, or Section 6.1.",
+      "command": "set -e\ngit show 964fe48:ecosystem/07_progress_comparison.md | grep -Fq 'version: 0.1.1'\ngit show 964fe48:ecosystem/07_progress_comparison.md | grep -Fq 'exactly one of four transition classes'\nfor tok in '`persisting`' '### 3.1 Pre-Window-Resolved' '### 3.2 First-Comparison' '### 6.1 Open-Findings Count'; do\n  if git show 964fe48:ecosystem/07_progress_comparison.md | grep -Fq \"$tok\"; then echo \"VACUITY: '$tok' already at base\"; exit 1; fi\ndone\necho 'E01 PASS: at base 964fe48 ecosystem/07 was 0.1.1 with four transition classes and none of persisting / 3.1 / 3.2 / 6.1 (anti-vacuity, every claimed absence checked)'"
+    },
+    {
+      "acceptance_test": "PERSISTING CLASS DEFINED: Section 3 now classifies into five transition classes and defines `persisting` as present-on-both-sides with CURRENT (freshly re-confirmed) evidence -- the exact opposite of `stale`.",
+      "command": "set -e\ngrep -Fq 'exactly one of five transition classes' ecosystem/07_progress_comparison.md\ngrep -Fq '`persisting` -- present in both executions and still open' ecosystem/07_progress_comparison.md\ngrep -Fq 'exact opposite of `stale`' ecosystem/07_progress_comparison.md\ngrep -Fq 'carried, not moved' ecosystem/07_progress_comparison.md\necho 'E02 PASS: Section 3 defines the fifth class persisting (present-on-both, current evidence, opposite of stale)'"
+    },
